36. ROWLAND.—Burton calls the last Abbot Richard Blyton, and Gill inserts the name as “Richard (or Rowland de) Bly— ton.” However‚ there is no real uncertainty as to what his name was. It occurs almost twenty times in Conventual Leases, and always under one or other of the forms Roland or Rowland. The earliest mention of him 1 meet with there is in No. 894, dated February 26, 1534, and the latest in No. 885, dated J uly 14, 1538.
